California Daycare Fraud Investigation Dashboard

1,159 of 39,184
Facilities Flagged for Potential Fraud
Child Care Centers: 19,426 | Family Child Care Homes: 19,758
Disclaimer: This dashboard is for investigative and research purposes only. The presence of a facility on this list does not constitute an accusation of fraud. Risk scores are based on patterns commonly associated with fraudulent operations, but further investigation is required to determine if any actual fraud has occurred. This tool is intended to assist investigators in identifying facilities that may warrant additional review.

Risk Scoring Methodology & Fraud Indicators

â–¼

This analysis uses patterns from the Minnesota "Feeding Our Future" fraud case ($250M) and San Diego UMI Learning Center case ($3.7M) to flag potentially fraudulent facilities.

Risk Score Calculation (0-10 scale)

FactorPointsWhy This Matters
COVID-Era License (2020-2022)+2Emergency funding with reduced oversight
Closed/Inactive Status+2Fraudulent facilities close quickly
Short Operation (<24 months)+3"Pop-up" fraud pattern
Shared Phone Number+2Multiple facilities, same controller
Generic Name+1Unremarkable names
